{"id": 232073110, "title": "Catastrophe Bond Issuance Hits Record Ahead of Hurricane Season", "text": "Issuance of catastrophe bonds just hit a record high, as the market braces for a rough hurricane season with the potential to do substantial damage. Sales of so-called cat bonds are 38% higher this year through May than over the same five-month period in 2023, which was already a record, according to Artemis, a compiler of data on insurance-linked securities. What\u2019s more, the $4 billion issued in May alone represents the greatest volume of catastrophe bonds ever sold in a single month, Artemis said.", "summary": "<a href=\"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMicmh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmJsb29tYmVyZy5jb20vbmV3cy9hcnRpY2xlcy8yMDI0LTA2LTA5L2NhdGFzdHJvcGhlLWJvbmQtaXNzdWFuY2UtaGl0cy1yZWNvcmQtYWhlYWQtb2YtaHVycmljYW5lLXNlYXNvbtIBAA?oc=5\" target=\"_blank\">Catastrophe Bond Issuance Hits Record Ahead of Hurricane Season</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color=\"#6f6f6f\">Bloomberg</font>", "url": "https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-06-09/catastrophe-bond-issuance-hits-record-ahead-of-hurricane-season", "image": "https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/ixD9lAoc03pM/v2/1200x800.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:31:35", "author": "Gautam Naik", "authors": ["Gautam Naik"], "language": "en", "source_country": "us", "sentiment": -0.127}